<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}+{9}{y}=-{34}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}+{9}{y}={22}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{7},-{3}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{x}+{9}{y}=-{34}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{x}=-{34}-{\left({9}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{34}-{\left({9}{y}\right)}}}{{1}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{\left(\frac{{-{34}-{\left({9}{y}\right)}}}{{1}}\right)}+{9}{y}={22}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{7}}{{1}}\cdot{\left(-{34}\right)}--\frac{{7}}{{1}}{\left({9}\right)}{y}+{9}{y}={22}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{238}-{\left({63}\right)}{y}+{9}{y}={22}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{63}{y}+{\left({9}\right)}{y}={22}-{238}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{63}{y}+{\left({9}\right)}{y}=-{216}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({63}+{\left({9}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{216}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{72}{y}=-{216}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{216}}{{72}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{3}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{x}+{9}{\left(-{3}\right)}=-{34}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{x}+{\left(-{27}\right)}=-{34}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{x}=-{34}-{\left(-{27}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{x}=-{7}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{7}}{{1}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{7}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{7},-{3}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

